          (<span class="opacity-60">
            <span class="text-[#f84f00]">web</span>,{' '}
            <span>mobile</span>, <span>üõ†Ô∏è</span>
          </span>)
        </span>
      </h1>

      <!-- Author Cards -->
      <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap gap-6">
        <!-- Profile -->
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 py-3 pr-3">
          <div
            class="relative h-16 w-16 overflow-hidden rounded-full bg-linear-to-br from-gray-600 to-gray-700"
          >
            <img
              src={meImage.src}
              alt="Profile"
              class="h-full w-full object-cover"
              loading="eager"
            />
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xl font-semibold">Gohit Bastian</div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm opacity-60">
              <span>@gohitx</span>
              <div class="flex gap-1">
                <a
                  href="https://twitter.com/gohitx"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="transition-colors hover:text-[#f84f00]"
                >
                  <TwitterIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
                </a>
                <a
                  href="https://github.com/gohitx"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="transition-colors hover:text-[#f84f00]"
                >
                  <GitHubIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8 leading-relaxed opacity-80">
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <p>
          Hello üëã, my name is{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold opacity-100">Gohit</span>,{' '}
          <span class="italic">I'm from Peru üáµüá™</span> and I'm a Frontend developer (Web & Mobile). I'm
          also a content creator focused on software and a bit of hardware. I also contribute to open
          source in different communities with extensions for VS Code, Linux, and more. My favorite tools
          right now are{' '}
          <span class="font-bold opacity-100">Next.js</span> for the web and <span
            class="font-bold opacity-100">Expo</span
          > for mobile applications (Learning Lynxjs).
        </p>

        <p>
          I'm the creator and maintainer of multiple extensions available on{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold opacity-100">VS Code</span> ‚Ä¢ Cursor ‚Ä¢ Windsurf ‚Ä¢ Trae.ai ‚Ä¢ Kiro
          & Firebase Studio, etc. If you want to learn more or install the extensions, you can find them{
            ' '
          }
          <a
            class="text-blue-400 hover:underline"
            href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/publishers/bastndev"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            here
          </a>
          .
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- TODO:  -->
      <div class="my-8 flex items-center justify-center gap-4 pt-10">
        <div class="flex-1 border-t border-dashed border-current opacity-20"></div>
        <span
          class="rounded-lg bg-[#363636] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          Latest Article
        </span>
        <div class="flex-1 border-t border-dashed border-current opacity-20"></div>
      </div>
      <!-- TODO:  -->

      <!-- MARK: Articles-->
      <div class="space-y-8 leading-relaxed opacity-80">
        <!-- Section Title -->
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">Currently Working On - Linux üíõ</h2>

        <p>
          Selecting a Linux distribution shouldn't require days of research and trial-and-error. Our
          smart selector asks simple questions about your hardware‚ÄîRAM, CPU, storage‚Äîand your use
          case, whether it's gaming, development, privacy, or just daily browsing. Within seconds,
          you get personalized recommendations tailored to your machine. No more downloading distros
          that won't boot or run sluggishly. We believe that finding the right Linux distribution
          should be{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold italic opacity-100"> effortless and instant </span>
          .
        </p>

        <p>
          Once you've found your ideal distribution, the next challenge is getting it onto a
          bootable USB drive. Traditional methods involve downloading ISOs, finding third-party
          tools like{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold">Rufus</span> or{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold italic">Etcher</span>, and hoping nothing goes wrong during the
          process. Our platform simplifies this entirely‚Äîselect your distro, choose your USB drive,
          and we handle the rest. From download to bootable creation, everything happens in one
          place, eliminating the need for multiple tools or technical knowledge. We believe testing
          Linux distributions should be{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold italic opacity-100"> as simple as a few clicks </span>
          .
        </p>

        <p>
          Beyond selection and installation, understanding what makes each Linux distribution unique
          is crucial. Our comprehensive database catalogs hundreds of distributions with detailed
          specifications‚Äîminimum{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold opacity-100">RAM requirements</span>, recommended{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold opacity-100">CPU architectures</span>, storage needs, desktop
          environments, and package managers. Compare{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold opacity-100">Debian</span> stability against <span
            class="font-semibold opacity-100">Arch</span
          >{' '}
          bleeding-edge updates, or explore lightweight options like{' '}
          <span class="font-semibold opacity-100">Puppy Linux</span> for older hardware. Every distro
          includes user reviews, use-case recommendations, and community ratings. We believe informed
          choices lead to better experiences, and finding your perfect Linux match should be backed by{
            ' '
          }
          <span class="font-semibold italic opacity-100"> complete, accessible information </span>
          . Explore the full catalog at{' '}
          <a href="/linux" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline"> Linux </a>
